  "questionId": "gfg-sub-aptitude-numbers",
  "title": "Numbers in Maths",
  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Numbers are symbols we use to count, measure, and describe things. They are everywhere in our daily lives and help us understand and organize the world. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Here are some simple ways numbers show up in our lives:</span></p><gfg-carousel><gfg-carousel-content alt=\"numbers_in_daily_life.webp\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250901163942171489/numbers_in_daily_life.webp\" width=\"800\"></gfg-carousel-content><gfg-carousel-content alt=\"numbers_as_tools.webp\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250901163941780370/numbers_as_tools.webp\" width=\"800\"></gfg-carousel-content><gfg-carousel-content alt=\"big_numbers.webp\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20250901163941518436/big_numbers.webp\" width=\"800\"></gfg-carousel-content></gfg-carousel><p dir=\"ltr\"><br/><span>Beyond everyday use, numbers are also fundamental mathematical entities that serve as the basis for counting, measuring, labeling, and performing calculations. They allow us to quantify and order the world, forming the foundation of mathematics and science.</span></p><h2 id=\"basics-of-numbers\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Basics of Numbers</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Learn the fundamental concepts needed to understand how numbers are used in counting, comparing, ordering, and representing quantities in everyday life and mathematics.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/counting-in-maths/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Counting in Maths</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/number-names-1-to-100/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Numbers in Words </span></a><span> </span></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/place-value-maths/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Place Value</span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/comparing-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Comparing Numbers</span></a></li><li value=\"5\"><span>Ordering Numbers: </span><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/ascending-order/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Ascending </span></a><span>&amp; </span><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/descending-order/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Decending</span></a></li><li value=\"6\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/real-life-applications-of-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Numbers in Real Life</span></a></li></ul><h2 id=\"types-of-numbers\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Types of Numbers</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span> Classify numbers into groups based on their properties and uses.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/types-of-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Classification of Numbers</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/even-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Even</span></a><span> and </span><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/odd-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Odd Numbers</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/prime-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Prime</span></a><span> and </span><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/composite-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Composite Numbers</span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/co-prime-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Co Prime Numbers</span></a></li><li value=\"5\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/perfect-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Perfect Numbers</span></a></li></ul><h2 id=\"operations-on-numbers\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Operations on Numbers</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Numbers can be combined using operations such as:</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/addition/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Addition </span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/subtraction/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Subtraction</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/multiplication/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Multiplication</span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/division/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Division</span></a></li></ul><h2 id=\"properties-of-numbers\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Properties of Numbers</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Different sets of numbers follow specific mathematical properties that help us perform operations and solve problems systematically.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/properties-of-real-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Properties of Real Numbers</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/properties-of-whole-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Properties of Whole Numbers</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/properties-of-rational-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Properties of Rational Numbers</span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/properties-of-integers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Properties of Integers</span></a></li></ul><h2 id=\"fun-facts-about-numbers\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Fun Facts About Numbers</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Numbers have many interesting patterns, these facts highlight the unique behavior of numbers in different contexts.</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/interesting-facts-about-natural-number/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Facts on Natural Numbers</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/amazing-facts-about-prime-numbers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Facts on Prime Numbers</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/interesting-fact-about-integers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Facts on Integers</span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/composite-numbers-interesting-facts/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Facts on Composite</span></a></li><li value=\"5\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/interesting-facts-about-decimals/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Facts on Decimals</span></a></li></ul><h2 id=\"number-system\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Number System</span></h2><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Numbers can also be written in different systems such as:</span></p><ul><li value=\"1\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/digital-logic/decimal-number-system/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Decimal Number System</span></a></li><li value=\"2\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/binary-number-system/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Binary Number System</span></a></li><li value=\"3\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/octal-number-system/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Octal Number System</span></a></li><li value=\"4\"><a href=\"#/articles/course/AptitudeCourses/gfg-sub-aptitude/maths/hexadecimal-number-system/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Hexadecimal Number System</span></a></li></ul>",
